==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nectarine
<hw>Nec`tar*ine"</hw> <pr>(n⟦ecr⟧k`t⟦etil⟧r*⟦emac⟧n")</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>nectarine</ets>. See
<er>Nectar</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A smooth-skinned variety
of peach.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Spanish nectarine</b></col>, <cd>the plumlike fruit of
the West Indian tree <spn>Chrysobalanus Icaco</spn>; -- also called
<altname>cocoa plum</altname>. It is made into a sweet conserve which is
largely exported from Cuba.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nectarize</ent>⟦br⟧
